Three ODM MPs from Homa Bay want governors in Nyanza to spearhead lifestyle audits in their counties to fight graft. John Mbadi (Suba South), Peter Kaluma (Homa Bay Town) and Millie Odhiambo (Suba North) said the county chiefs should take the lead. Mbadi spoke during the wedding of Lameck and Rose Ogolla in Homa Bay town.Â  Kaluma said on Sunday governors should be subjected to lifestyle audit to break the culture of bad governance. Odhiambo supported him. She said corruption hampers development in most counties.